gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 118, Bulls 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Giannis Antetokounmpo led the Bucks with 35 points (14 points in 4th quarter and 13-22 FG overall) and 11 rebounds as the Bucks defeated the Bulls, 118-109. Bobby Portis (19 points, 10 rebounds) and Khris Middleton (13 points, six rebounds) totaled 32 points for the Bucks as well. Nikola Vucevic tied a season-best 26 points, along with 12 rebounds and five assists as Zach LaVine added 20 points, eight rebounds, and five assists for the Bulls. The Bucks improve to 6-4 (5-1 at home) as the Bulls move to 4-7 on the year.
